d%20judges%20are%20forced%20to%20make%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20choices%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20issues%20coming%20to%20court%20are%20political%20issues%20dressed%20as%20legal%20issues.%20Judges%20do%20make%20political%20choices.%20They%20may%20think%20they%20are%20being%20neutral.%20Politics%20and%20judicial%20functioning%20are%20not%20as%20separate%20as%20we%20want%20them%20to%20be.%20They%20are%20getting%20increasingly%20mixed%20up.%20What%20we%20wear%2C%20what%20we%20eat%2C%20what%20we%20speak%20%E2%80%93%20they%20are%20all%20becoming%20constitutional%20issues%20now%20and%20judges%20are%20being%20forced%20to%20make%20a%20choice%2C%20and%20make%20that%20choice%20in%20public%2C%E2%80%9D%3Cem%3E%20Livelaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fjudges-do-make-political-choices-politics-judicial-functioning-not-as-separate-as-we-want-justice-retd-s-muralidhar-237829%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20Justice%20Muralidhar%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20made%20these%20remarks%20at%20a%20panel%20discussion%20held%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Thursday%2C%20September%2014%2C%20following%20the%20launch%20of%20lawyer%20Gautam%20Bhatia%E2%80%99s%20latest%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EUnsealed%20Covers%3A%20A%20Decade%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20Courts%2C%20and%20the%20State%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0The%20panel%20also%20included%20the%20author%2C%20renowned%20criminal%20lawyer%20Rebecca%20John%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20editor%20Seema%20Chishti.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20noting%20that%20the%20book%20sheds%20light%20on%20the%20intersection%20of%20politics%20and%20judicial%20decisions%2C%20he%20said%20judges%20are%20forced%20to%20take%20%E2%80%98definitive%20positions%E2%80%99%2C%20often%20making%20political%20choices%20on%20legal%20and%20constitutional%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhere%20do%20judges%20come%20from%3F%20Gautam%E2%80%99s%20writing%20tells%20you%20that%20they%20do%20come%20from%20definitive%20positions.%20This%20book%20tells%20you%20that%20there%20are%20many%20political%20issues%20coming%20to%20courts%20dressed%20as%20legal%20issues.%20The%20Hijab%20case%2C%20for%20instance.%20Today%20(Sep%2014)%2C%20we%20had%20two%20news%20items.%20One%20about%20the%20choice%20of%20food%20in%20Lakshadweep%20and%20another%20about%20the%20flying%20of%20flags%20in%20a%20temple%20in%20Kerala.%20Judges%20do%20make%20political%20choices%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20judge%20also%20acknowledged%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20legal%20correspondents%2C%20including%20stories%20getting%20shelved%20at%20the%20editorial%20stage.%20He%20also%20drew%20his%20attention%20to%20how%20%E2%80%9Cselective%20information%20leaks%E2%80%9D%20to%20certain%20news%20outlets%20could%20result%20in%20biased%20reporting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20legal%20correspondents%20have%20lamented%20about%20how%20many%20stories%20were%20killed%20at%20the%20editorial%20desk.%20It%20will%20be%20interesting%2C%20after%20reading%20Gautam%E2%80%99s%20book%20if%20someone%20brings%20out%20a%20volume%20of%20killed%20stories.%20That%20will%20tell%20us%20how%20much%20was%20kept%20back.%20Also%20interesting%20is%20how%20newspaper%20scoops%20are%20a%20result%C2%A0of%20the%20selective%20leaking%20of%20information%20to%20a%20particular%20newspaper.%20But%2C%20this%20distorts%20the%20way%20journalists%20are%20supposed%20to%20function%20and%20the%20bias%20creeps%20into%20their%20writing.%C2%A0You%20will%20find%20journalists%20fiercely%20defending%20the%20court%20with%20their%20pieces%2C%20and%20then%20you%20begin%20wondering%20about%20the%20news%20channel%20or%20newspaper%E2%80%99s%20objectivity%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustice%20Muralidhar%20retired%20as%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20Odisha%20high%20court%20on%20August%207.%20As%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DlVxqEaOZGhI%5C%22%3Eearlier%3C%2Fa%3