olitical%20and%20geoeconomic%20considerations%20guide%20Chinese%20ties%20with%20Nepal.%20In%202019%2C%20during%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Kathmandu%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20elevated%20their%20relationship%20to%20a%20%E2%80%98strategic%20partnership%20of%20cooperation%E2%80%99%2C%20featuring%20ever-lasting%20friendship%20for%20development%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmofa.gov.np%2Fjoint-statement-between-nepal-and-the-peoples-republic-of-china-2%2F%5C%22%3Eprosperity.%3C%2Fa%3E%20On%20the%20economic%20front%2C%20China%20is%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20largest%20source%20of%20foreign%20direct%20investment%20and%20its%20second%20largest%20trading%20partner%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fmoney%2F2023%2F03%2F14%2Fprime-minister-dahal-urges-china-to-invest-in-nepal%5C%22%3Eafter%20India.%3C%2Fa%3E%20In%202022%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20imports%20from%20China%20were%20%241.84%20billion%2C%20while%20exports%20totalled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fnepal-seeks-easier-trade-access-chinese-markets-2023-03-14%2F%5C%22%3E%245.39%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELoans%20not%20grants%3A%20a%20fear%20of%20falling%20into%20the%20%E2%80%98Chinese%20debt%20trap%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20major%20irritants%20between%20Beijing%20and%20Kathmandu%20is%20the%20projects%20under%20the%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiatives%20(BRI).%20In%202018%2C%20Kathmandu%20proposed%20a%20list%20of%2035%20projects%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20infrastructure%2C%20energy%20and%20power%2C%20north-south%20corridor%20upgradation%2C%20free%20trade%20areas%20and%20construction%20of%20integrated%20check%20posts%20at%20various%20Nepal-China%20border%20points%20under%20the%20BRI.%20Through%20such%20projects%2C%20Nepal%20aimed%20to%20bring%20an%20investment%20of%20around%20%2410%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20China%20did%20not%20agree%20on%20the%20proposed%20number%20of%20projects%2C%20which%20were%20finally%20trimmed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.isas.nus.edu.sg%2Fpapers%2Fnepals-foreign-policy-priorities%2F%5C%22%3Eto%20nine.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202022%2C%20then%20Chinese%20Ambassador%20to%20Nepal%2C%20Hou%20Yanqi%2C%20claimed%20that%20the%20three%20international%20airports%20%E2%80%93%20Gautam%20Buddha%20Airport%20in%20Lumbini%2C%20Pokhara%20Airport%2C%20and%20Tribhuvan%20International%20Airport%20%E2%80%93%20in%20Nepal%20are%20within%20the%20framework%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fnepal-seeks-easier-trade-access-chinese-markets-2023-03-14%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20BRI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20in%20June%202023%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20minister%20N.P.%20Saud%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fnational%2F2023%2F06%2F27%2Fnepal-yet-to-execute-bri-projects-says-foreign-minister-saud.%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20not%20even%20a%20single%20project%20under%20the%20BRI%20had%20been%20executed%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20clarity%20on%20the%20funding%20of%20the%20projects%20under%20the%20BRI%2C%20which%20has%20a%20loan%20component%20and%20not%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fcolumns%2F2023%2F09%2F11%2Fchina-nepal-and-the-bri-dilemma%5C%22%3Egrants.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENepal%E2%80%99s%20strategic%20significance%20for%20the%20US%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20study%20titled%20%3Cem%3EBanking%20on%20the%20Belt%20and%20Road%3A%20Insights%20from%20a%20new%20global%20dataset%20of%2013%2C427%20Chinese%20development%20projects%20%3C%2Fem%3Eby%20Ammar%20A.%20Malik%20et%20al.%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.aiddata.org%2Fad4%2Fpdfs%2FBanking_on_the_Belt_and_Road__Insights_from_a_new_global_dataset_of_13427_Chinese_development_projects.pdf%5C%22%3EAidData%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20the%20average%20interest%20rate%20of%20a%20loan%20from%20an%20official%20sector%20in%20China%20is%204.2%25%2C%20while%20the%20average%20maturity%20length%20is%209.4%20years%20and%20the%20average%20grace%20period%20is%201.8%20years.%20This%20is%20much%20higher%20than%20the%20soft%20loans%20from%20World%20Bank%20and%20the%20Asian%20Development%20Bank%2C%20which%20have%20a%20maximum%20interest%20rate%20of%201.3%25%20and%20a%20longer%20repayment%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fcolumns%2F2023%2F09%2F11%2Fchina-nepal-and-the-bri-dilemma%5C%22%3Eperiod.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20difference%20in%20the%20interest%20rates%20create%20fear%20among%20many%20small%20countries%20of%20falling%20into%20%E2%80%9CChina%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.project-syndicate.org%2Fcommentary%2Fchina-one-belt-one-road-loans-debt-by-brahma-chellaney-2017-01%3Fbarrier%3Daccesspaylog%5C%22%3Edebt%20trap%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%3B%20however%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20third%20white%20paper%20on%20foreign%20aid%2C%20%3Cem%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20International%20Development%20Cooperation%20in%20the%20New%20Era%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Epublished%20in%202021%2C%20talks%20about%20increasing%20aid%20to%20developing%20countries%20within%20the%20BRI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.www.gov.cn%2Farchive%2Fwhitepaper%2F202101%2F10%2Fcontent_WS5ffa6bbbc6d0f72576943922.html%5C%22%3Eframework.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20power%20contest%20has%20reignited%20in%20Asia%2C%20with%20Nepal%20acquiring%20strategic%20significance%20for%20Washington%20D.C.%20Like%20BRI%2C%20Nepal%20agreed%20on%20the%20Millennium%20Challenge%20Corporation%20(MCC)%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mcc.gov%2Fnews-and-events%2Fevent%2Fsigning-091417-nepal%5C%22%3ESeptember%202017%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ratified%20it%20on%20February%2027%2C%202022%2C%20with%2012%20interpretative%20declarations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20agreement%2C%20MCC%2C%20an%20independent%20aid%20agency%20of%20the%20US%2C%20will%20bear%20the%20cost%20of%20%24500%20million%20and%20Nepal%20will%20provide%20%24130%20million%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fwhy-is-us-infrastructure-grant-behind-protests-nepal-2022-02-24%2F%5C%22%3Evarious%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Post-MCC%2C%20some%20important%20US%20officials%2C%20such%20as%20Under%20Secretary%20of%20State%20for%20Political%20Affairs%2C%20Victoria%20Nuland%2C%20and%20Assistant%20Secretary%20for%20South%20and%20Central%20Asia%2C%20Donald%20Lu%2C%20visited%20Kathmandu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20role%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20China%20and%20the%20US%2C%20India%20is%20an%20important%20country%20for%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022-23%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20exports%20to%20Nepal%20were%20around%20%248%20billion%2C%20while%20its%20imports%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Findia-nepal-will-resolve-all-issues-as-bilateral-relations-grow-to-touch-himalayan-heights-modi%2Farticle66919438.ece%5C%22%3E%24840%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%20India%20has%20provided%20a%20transit%20facility%20to%20landlocked%20Nepal%20to%20carry%20out%20trade%20with%20a%20third%20country.%20To%20enhance%20their%20bilateral%20ties%2C%20during%20Prachanda%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20New%20Delhi%20in%20May-June%20this%20year%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20kept%20political%20disputes%20and%20differences%20over%20territory%20aside%20and%20inked%20important%20memorandums%20of%20understanding%20%2Fagreements%20and%20launched%20important%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fbilateral-documents.htm%3Fdtl%2F36632%2FList_of_Outcomes_Official_visit_of_Prime_Minister_of_Nepal_to_India.%2F%5C%22%3Eprojects%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20ties%20had%20deteriorated%20after%20India%20carried%20out%20an%20economic%20blockade%20that%20lasted%20for%20about%20four%20and%20a%20half%20months%20in%202015-16.%20Due%20to%20this%2C%20Nepal%20had%20suffered%20a%20loss%20of%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fmoney%2F2016%2F06%2F21%2Fblockade-by-india-resulted-in-losses-totalling-rs202-billion%5C%22%3E%241.96%20billion.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Then%20there%20was%20a%20row%20over%20India%E2%80%99s%20updated%20map%20released%20in%202019%2C%20showing%20Kalapani%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2019%2F11%2F8%2Findias-updated-political-map-stirs-controversy-in-nepal%5C%22%3Eterritory.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Nevertheless%2C%20India%20and%20Nepal%20share%20close%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeijing%20has%20often%20publicly%20reacted%20over%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20growing%20ties%20with%20the%20US%20and%20its%20deep%20relations%20with%20India.%20For%20instance%2C%20after%20Nepal%20ratified%20the%20MCC%2C%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20spokeswoman%20Hua%20Chunying%20called%20it%20a%20Pandora%E2%80%99s%20box%20and%20said%20that%20China%20believes%20that%20international%20development%20cooperation%20should%20be%20based%20on%20the%20principle%20of%20mutual%20respect%2C%20equality%2C%20and%20that%20the%20sovereignty%20of%20the%20country%20should%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.setopati.com%2Fpolitical%2F158002%5C%22%3Erespected.%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommenting%20on%20India%2C%20while%20addressing%20the%20audience%20in%20a%20discussion%20titled%20%E2%80%98China%20in%20global%20economy%20and%20its%20impact%20in%20Nepal%E2%80%99%2C%20held%20by%20the%20Foundation%20for%20Trans-Himalayan%20Research%20and%20Studies%20and%20Friends%20of%20Silk%20Road%20Club%20Nepal%20at%20Kathmandu%2C%20Chinese%20ambassador%20to%20Nepal%2C%20Chen%20Song%2C%20ignited%20a%20controversy%20after%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CUnfortunately%2C%20you%20have%20a%20neighbour%20like%20India%2C%20but%20fortunately%20you%20have%20a%20neighbour%20like%20India%2C%20because%20India%20is%20a%20huge%20market%20with%20a%20huge%20potential%20you%20can%20tap%20in%20to%E2%80%A6But%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20policy%20towards%20Nepal%20and%20other%20neighbours%20is%20not%20so%20friendly%20and%20not%20so%20beneficial%20to%20Nepal.%20So%20we%20call%20that%20a%20policy%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fnational%2F2023%2F09%2F07%2Fchinese-ambassador-takes-flak-for-his-remarks-on-nepal-india-relations%5C%22%3Econstraints%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20likely%20be%20an%20emphasis%20on%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20economic%20needs%20and%20China%E2%80%99s%20strategic%20investment%20during%20Prachanda%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Beijing.%20Nepal%20needs%20execution%20of%20the%20projects%20planned%20under%20the%20BRI%20framework%20and%20may%20ask%20for%20more%20Chinese%20investment%20in%20various%20sectors%20for%20its%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Chinese%20will%20mainly%20be%20interested%20in%20having%20a%20friendly%20government%20in%20Kathmandu%20which%20can%20appropriately%20address%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20political%2C%20economic%2C%20and%20strategic%20interests%20in%20Nepal.%20Kathmandu%20has%20reiterated%20that%20it%20aims%20to%20have%20a%20balanced%20relation%20with%20India%20and%20China.%20However%2C%20it%20appears%20to%20be%20difficult%20to%20do%20that%20for%20a%20very%20long%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmit%20Ranjan%20is%20a%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20Institute%20of%20South%20Asian%20Studies%2C%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694779539000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F07141514%2FPrachanda-Dahal.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fwill-nepal-pms-upcoming-visit-to-beijing-balance-geopolitical-interests-for-india-and-china%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Unlike%202008%2C%20when%20Prachanda%20chose%20Beijing%20as%20his%20first%20foreign%20capital%20as%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister%2C%20in%202016%20and%202023%2C%20he%20maintained%20the%20tradition%20of%20visiting%20India%20first.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fwill-nepal-pms-upcoming-visit-to-beijing-balance-geopolitical-interests-for-india-and-china%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22TikTok%20fined%20%E2%82%AC345m%20over%20handling%20of%20children's%20data%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694779440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F19%2F07%2F768x432%2Fskynews-tik-tok-logo_4708067.jpg%3F20190702170546%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftiktok-fined-8364345m-over-handling-of-childrens-data-12961803%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22TikTok%20has%20been%20fined%20%E2%82%AC345m%20(%C2%A3296m)%20for%20breaching%20privacy%20laws%20over%20the%20processing%20of%20children's%20personal%20data%2C%20an%20EU%20regulator%20has%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A88%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftiktok-fined-eur345m-over-handling-of-childrens-data-12961803%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ftiktok-fined-eur345m-over-handling-of-childrens-data-12961803%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ftiktok-fined-eur345m-over-handling-of-childrens-data-12961803%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election%2C%20One%20Leader%2C%20One%20Faith%2C%20One%20Business%20House%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F17091827%2FIMG_4750.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdogan%20was%20%E2%80%98re-elected%E2%80%99%20Turkey%E2%80%99s%20president%20in%20May%20this%20year%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fpm-modi-erdogan-turkey-president-turkey-elections-101685334010171.html%5C%22%3Eamong%20the%20first%20to%20congratulate%20him%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Erdogan%2C%20whom%20western%20analysts%20call%20an%20elected%20dictator%2C%20has%20been%20continuously%20in%20power%20for%2020%20years%2C%20first%20as%20prime%20minister%20and%20then%20as%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20he%20held%20a%20referendum%20to%20force%20a%20presidential%20system%20of%20government%20and%20won.%20Since%20then%2C%20he%20has%20continued%20as%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20all-powerful%20president.%20A%20closer%20look%20will%20reveal%20how%20Modi%20has%20taken%20Erdogan%20as%20a%20role%20model%20and%20heavily%20borrowed%20from%20him%20things%20like%20minority%20bashing%20(Kurds)%20and%20a%20Hindutva%20vote%20bank%20(orthodox%20Islamists)%2C%20and%20now%20a%20%E2%80%98system%20change%E2%80%99%2C%20too%2C%20appears%20in%20the%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Erdogan%2C%20Modi%20made%20all%20statutory%20watchdogs%20and%20constitutional%20positions%20ineffective%20by%20simply%20appointing%20favourites.%20This%20is%20the%20reason%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20India%20finds%20itself%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-no-longer-democracy-electoral-autocracy-v-dem-institute-report-bjp-narendra-modi%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20same%20unflattering%20lists%20as%20Turkey%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20a%20position%20no%20democracy%20would%20like%20to%20find%20itself%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20what%20is%20quantifiable%2C%20Modi%20has%20also%20borrowed%20from%20his%20fellow%20dictator%E2%80%99s%20playbook%20three%20further%20elements%3A%20stealth%2C%20subterfuge%20and%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20background%20in%20which%20one%20has%20to%20assess%20the%20recent%20series%20of%20gambits%20by%20the%20Modi%20regime.%20Look%20at%20the%20way%20the%20special%20session%20of%20parliament%20was%20called%20and%20how%20the%20country%20was%20kept%20in%20suspense%20over%20its%20purpose.%20The%20very%20strength%20of%20parliament%20is%20its%20openness.%20Yet%20suddenly%20on%20August%2031%2C%20the%20parliamentary%20affairs%20minister%20parliamentary%20affairs%20minister%20Prahlad%20Joshi%20announced%2C%20rather%20oddly%2C%20through%20social%20media%2C%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-government-calls-five-day-special-session-of-parliament-from-september-18%5C%22%3Ea%20special%20session%20of%20parliament%20would%20be%20held%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20September%2018%20to%2022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fparliament-special-session-question-hour-private-members-business-one-nation-one-election-2430243-2023-09-03%5C%22%3Ewithout%20question%20hour%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agenda%20of%20the%20session%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-issues-will-the-5-day-special-session-take-up-no-one-knows-not-even-the-cabinet%5C%22%3Ewas%20kept%20a%20secret%3C%2Fa%3E%20till%20Wednesday%2C%20September%2013%2C%20leading%20to%20much%20speculation%20about%20the%20agenda.%20Even%20now%2C%20the%20stated%20agenda%20%E2%80%93%20to%20%E2%80%98review%20the%20parliamentary%20journey%20of%2075%20years%20since%20the%20Samvidhan%20Sabha%20%E2%80%98%20%E2%80%93%20is%20vague.%20And%20the%20government%20has%20already%20said%20the%20published%20items%20of%20business%20should%20not%20be%20considered%20%E2%80%98exhaustive%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Simultaneous%20Elections%3A%20Why%20Now%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fsimultaneous-elections-why-now%5C%22%3ESimultaneous%20Elections%3A%20Why%20Now%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20if%20the%20the%20secrecy%20about%20the%20agenda%20was%20not%20bad%20enough%2C%C2%A0%20Joshi%20announced%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcommittee-on-simultaneous-polls%5C%22%3Epanel%20headed%20by%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20study%20the%20possibility%20of%20one-nation%20one-election.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20an%20eight-member%20panel%20which%20included%20Amit%20Shah%20was%20formally%20notified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20announcement%20had%20all%20the%20trappings%20of%20an%20archetypal%20authoritarian%20style.%20Kovind%20was%20in%20fact%20deputed%20by%20Shah%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fnation%2F2023%2Fsep%2F05%2Fformer-president-kovind-began-one-nation-one-election-spade-work-in-june-2611779.html%5C%22%3Eas%20early%20as%20June%202%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20soon%20after%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Karnataka%20shock%20defeat.%20Moreover%2C%20that%20was%20a%20time%20when%20a%20formidable%20opposition%20alliance%20was%20taking%20shape.%20Kovind%20had%20accordingly%20met%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%2C%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20Lok%20Sabha%20speaker%20Om%20Birla%2C%20RSS%20chief%20Mohan%20Bhagwat%20and%20a%20dozen%20state%20governors.%20A%20highly%20unusual%20schedule%20for%20a%20former%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20the%20official%20notification%20came%20several%20weeks%20after%20considerable%20spadework%20had%20already%20begun.%20Why%20this%20secrecy%3F%20To%20upstage%20the%20opposition%3F%20And%20all%20the%20eight%20members%20on%20the%20committee%20constituted%20in%20a%20dictatorial%20style%20are%20known%20to%20be%20government%20supporters.%20The%20only%20member%20from%20the%20other%20side%2C%20Congress%20leader%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chaudhary%2C%20resigned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20days%20after%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20one%20country%20one%20election%20gambit%2C%20came%20another%20surprise.%20Suddenly%2C%20we%20found%20President%20Droupadi%20Murmu%E2%80%99s%20invitation%20for%20a%20Rashtrapati%20Bhavan%20dinner%20for%20foreign%20dignitaries%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fpresident-of-bharat-g20-invitation%5C%22%3Edescribing%20her%20as%20%E2%80%98President%20of%20Bharat%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20was%20another%20display%20of%20a%20typical%20authoritarian%20trait.%20Subsequently%2C%20documents%20relating%20to%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Indonesia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wionews.com%2Findia-news%2Findonesia-refers-to-modi-as-pm-of-bharat-in-invitation-letter-to-asean-summit-632900%5C%22%3Ealso%20had%20%E2%80%98Bharat%E2%80%99%20instead%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20such%20a%20display%20of%20unannounced%20%E2%80%98nationalism%E2%80%99%20only%20for%20the%20foreign%20ministry%20and%20the%20Rashtrapati%3F%20Will%20%E2%80%98Bharat%E2%80%99%20replace%20%E2%80%98India%E2%80%99%20everywhere%3F%20In%20orderly%20democracies%20with%20wide%20linguistic%20and%20cultural%20diversities%2C%20such%20decisions%20are%20taken%20after%20due%20deliberation%2C%20not%20via%20authoritarian%20PMO%20decrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20triple%20jolts%20seems%20to%20have%20badly%20shaken%20the%20Modi%20establishment%20%E2%80%94%20consolidation%20of%20the%20opposition%20into%20a%20formidable%20challenge%2C%20the%20shock%20defeat%20in%20Karnataka%20and%20the%20Adani%20entanglement.%20Consider%20the%20panic%20moves%20which%20came%20in%20quick%20succession%2C%20to%20remove%20the%20remaining%20hurdles%20in%20the%20way%20of%20total%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20CJI%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20now%20a%20nominated%20member%20of%20parliament%2C%20in%20his%20only%20intervention%20in%20the%20house%20to%20date%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Franjan-gogoi-rajya-sabha-first-speech%5C%22%3Equestioned%20the%20very%20maintainability%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20constitution%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20he%20got%20ready%20support%20from%20TV%20anchors%20and%20various%20regime-friendly%20writers%20in%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20came%20the%20proposal%20for%20a%20new%20constitution%20for%20India.%20Bibek%20Debroy%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20PM%E2%80%99s%20economic%20advisory%20council%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fopinion%2Fonline-views%2Ftheres-a-case-for-we-the-people-to-embrace-a-new-constitution-11692021963182.html%5C%22%3E%20in%20an%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20floated%20the%20idea%20that%20India%20needed%20a%20new%20constitution.%C2%A0%20He%20cited%20the%20changing%20requirements%20as%20reason%20for%20this.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20should%20go%20back%20to%20the%20drawing%20board%20and%20start%20from%20first%20principles%2C%20asking%20what%20these%20words%20in%20the%20Preamble%20mean%20now%3A%20socialist%2C%20secular%2C%20democratic%2C%20justice%2C%20liberty%20and%C2%A0equality%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficial%20circles%20later%20clarified%20that%20this%20was%20Debroy%E2%80%99s%20personal%20view.%20But%20what%20fuelled%20suspicions%20that%20this%20was%20not%20is%20that%20Debroy%E2%80%99s%20views%20also%20got%20support%20from%20many%20other%20pro-establishment%20writers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20Act%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-law%2Fchief-election-commissioner-appointment-explained-supreme-court-ruling-8474745%2F%5C%22%3Ewas%20amended%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20create%20a%20selection%20panel%20%E2%80%93%20as%20mandated%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%E2%80%93%20but%20the%20government%20decided%20not%20to%20include%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20as%20a%20member%2C%20as%20the%20court%20had%20suggested.%20The%20amendment%20ensures%20a%20majority%20for%20the%20government%20side%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20filling%20the%20Election%20Commission%20with%20favourites%20%E2%80%93%20now%20through%20a%20supposedly%20legitimate%20search%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20establishing%20full%20control%20over%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20it%20is%20the%20turn%20of%20saffronisation%20of%20law.%20In%20true%20authoritarian%20style%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20introduced%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%2C%20Nagrik%20Suraksha%20and%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20bills%20to%20replace%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%2C%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20and%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%20without%20consulting%20the%20oppo